<p>It’s that time—to begin the process of finding the next editor of <italic>Teaching Sociology</italic>. The call for the new editor is on <bold>p. 339</bold> of this issue. If you are considering applying, please know that I will be happy to answer any of your questions. Just email me and we can have an email conversation or a telephone one. I also am creating a standard FAQ about being the <italic>TS</italic> editor that I will share with all persons who contact me.</p>
<p>I want to thank everyone for their patience as I recovered from my knee replacement surgery in early May. A special thank you to Rosie Ponce, my managing editor for several years, for stepping up to help process manuscripts in a timely manner, even as she was graduating with her Master of Social Work degree.</p>
<p>Enjoy your summer!</p>
